CBS political analyst John Dickerson has been announced as the new host of Face the Nation
taking over from veteran broadcaster Bob Schieffer
The Chief Political Correspondent of Slate Magazine was announced as the new host on the show on Sunday after the 78-year-old announced he would be retiring last week
ending Schieffer 's 14-year reign as host of the long-running news program
after announcing his retirement from CBS News at the close of the Schieffer Symposium on the News at TCU .
